> I just pulled apart a spare engine I have and am wondering if anyone would
>know what the piston numbers mean. The numbers are 1275 and 095107+ 9 7 all
>the pistons have the same markings. Will this number tell me displacement
>and if so does anyone want to guess on the engine size.
>
> Also the case number is 32 VW 000 101 102 is this an late case good for
>rebuilding? I would like to rebuild this engine and put it into my 21 window
>but I am just starting off and don't know if this case is worth the effort.
>
>PS: This is my first Engine Rebuild Attempt so please bare with me.

Erik: Keep your shorts on ! ( "bare with me" ? ) I think not.
Both #'s are casting # "s and relatively meaningless for your
purpose of identification. The  engine # is on the case below
the generator stand, and the piston diameter measurement
is what you need, it is on the piston top surface ( or get a ruler ).
Dave \X/


